@11003 = ~Shield

Duration: 5 turns
Area of Effect: The wearer

When this ability is cast, an invisible barrier comes into being in front of the character. It sets the character's Armor Class to 4 against all melee weapons, and 2 against missile weapons. It also grants the character immunity from the spell Magic Missile. The effect lasts for the duration of the ability or until dispelled.~
@11004 = ~Mind Shield

Duration: 1 turn
Area of Effect: The wearer

This ability renders the character immune to magical commands. The character becomes immune to charm, confusion, fear, domination, ESP, Know Alignment, hold, stun, psionics, sleep, and feeblemind.~
@11005 = ~Cure Poison

Range: Touch
Duration: Instant
Area of Effect: 1 creature

This ability removes all toxins from the body, both natural and magical in nature. When this ability is cast upon a poisoned individual, it immediately neutralizes any poison.~
@11006 = ~Improved Haste

Duration: 23 rounds
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: The wearer

The character functions at double its normal movement and attack rates and receives a +2 bonus to its initiative. Thus, the character moving at 6 and attacking once per round would move at 12 and attack twice per round. Spellcasting and spell effects are not sped up. There are two major differences between the 3rd-level wizard spell Haste and this ability: First, there is no period of fatigue following the expiration of the ability; second, this ability actually doubles the number of attacks per round of the hasted character. This ability also negates the effects of a Slow spell, but it is not cumulative with itself or with other similar magic. Its effects will last for the duration or until dispelled.~
